results.lead_paragraph: Devastated by news that I am taking a three-week vacation which will leave them bereft of comfort and wisdom until March, hordes are standing outside my office at this very moment sobbing and pleading for me not to go. "How," they ask, "are we to survive this deprivation?" Such is the selfishness of the multitude. Not one thinks of my own need to flee the calamity called February and frolic in the hibiscus while all Florida kowtows to my mighty credit cards.
